[{"id":41037,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["-235","-253","-100","-20"],"answer":1,"solution":"The root-mean-square speed of gas molecules is: $v_{rms} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT}{M}}$, where $T$ is absolute temperature and $M$ is molar mass.<br><br>For oxygen at $T_1 = 47°C = 320$ K with $M_{O_2} = 32$ g/mol:<br>$v_{rms,O_2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3R(320)}{32}}$<br><br>For hydrogen with $M_{H_2} = 2$ g/mol at temperature $T_2$:<br>$v_{rms,H_2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT_2}{2}}$<br><br>Equating the RMS speeds:<br>$\\sqrt{\\frac{3R(320)}{32}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT_2}{2}}$<br><br>$\\frac{320}{32} = \\frac{T_2}{2}$<br><br>$T_2 = 2 \\times 10 = 20$ K<br><br>Converting to Celsius: $t_2 = 20 - 273 = -253°C$, which is option (2).","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (21 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41043,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{25}{4}$","$\\frac{2}{5}$","$\\frac{5}{2}$","$\\frac{4}{25}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"(Vapor density) $=\\left(\\frac{\\text { Molar mass }}{2}\\right)$, I.e, $v d=\\frac{M}{2}$\n$\\begin{aligned} & v_{\\mathrm{rms}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{3 R T}{M}} \\\\ & \\frac{v_2}{v_1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{M_1}{M_2}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{25}{4}}=\\frac{5}{2}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41107,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>249</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>1</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>For gas A</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>RT</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>for gas <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>RT</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Now according to the Dalton&#39;s law of mixture,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41087,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Momentum is a vector quantity and average momentum of molecules of a sample is zero due to random motion.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mrow><mi>avg</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>RMS speed of a molecule is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Now the temperature is doubled&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi>new</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></math>&nbsp;and due to dissociation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>new</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>new</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>new</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>v</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41048,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$70 \\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\mathrm{T}$","$35 \\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\mathrm{T}$","$\\frac{7}{2} \\mathrm{RT}$","$35 \\mathrm{RT}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Degree of freedom }(f)=5+2(3 \\mathrm{~N}-5) \\\\\n& \\qquad f=5+2(3 \\times 2-1)=7 \\\\\n& \\text { energy of one molecule }=\\frac{f}{2} K_B T\n\\end{aligned}$\nenergy of 10 molecules\n$=10\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{f}}{2} \\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\mathrm{T}\\right)=10\\left(\\frac{7}{2} \\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\mathrm{T}\\right)=35 \\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\mathrm{T}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41059,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Now, for mixture</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mtext>mixture </mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>19</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>γ</mi><mtext>mixture </mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mtext>mixture</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mn>19</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>29</mn><mn>19</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41035,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{O}_{2}$","$\\mathrm{NH}_{3}$","$\\mathrm{CO}_{2}$","He"],"answer":3,"solution":"For an adiabatic process ($\\Delta Q = 0$) with an ideal gas: $TV^{\\gamma-1} = \\text{constant}$<br>Given: $V_f = 8V_i$ and $T_f = \\frac{1}{4}T_i$<br>Applying the adiabatic relation:<br>$T_i V_i^{\\gamma-1} = T_f V_f^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$T_i V_i^{\\gamma-1} = \\frac{T_i}{4}(8V_i)^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$1 = \\frac{1}{4} \\cdot 8^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$4 = 8^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$2^2 = 2^{3(\\gamma-1)}$<br>$2 = 3(\\gamma-1)$<br>$\\gamma = \\frac{5}{3} = 1.67$<br>This value corresponds to a monatomic gas. Among the options, only He is monatomic ($\\gamma = 5/3$ for monatomic ideal gases). O₂ and N₂ are diatomic ($\\gamma = 7/5$), CO₂ is polyatomic ($\\gamma \\approx 1.30$), and NH₃ is polyatomic.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41068,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>750</mn><mi>d</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1098</mn><mi>d</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2049</mn><mi>d</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1500</mn><mi>d</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The mean free path is given by the relation,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msub><mi>N</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></math>&nbsp;be the new mean free path.</p><p>Hence,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1500</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>273</mn><mn>373</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2049</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>2049</mn><mi>d</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41038,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$1: 10$","$10: 1$","$1: \\sqrt{10}$","$1: 1$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$K. E=\\frac{f}{2} K T$<br/>For He and $\\mathrm{Ar} \\mathrm{f}=3$<br/>$\\frac{\\mathrm{K} \\cdot \\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{He}}}{\\mathrm{~K} \\cdot \\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{Ar}}}=\\frac{1}{1}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41032,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$10 \\sqrt{2} \\times 10^{-8}$","$2 \\sqrt{2} \\times 10^{-8}$","$2 \\sqrt{2} \\times 10^{-10}$","$2 \\times 10^{-8}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Mean free path is calculated using $\\lambda = \\frac{k_B T}{\\sqrt{2} \\pi d^2 P}$<br>Given: $d = 5 \\times 10^{-10}$ m, $T = 41°C = 314$ K, $P = 1.38 \\times 10^5$ Pa, $k_B = 1.38 \\times 10^{-23}$ J/K<br>$\\lambda = \\frac{1.38 \\times 10^{-23} \\times 314}{\\sqrt{2} \\times \\pi \\times (5 \\times 10^{-10})^2 \\times 1.38 \\times 10^5}$<br>$= \\frac{1.38 \\times 10^{-23} \\times 314}{\\sqrt{2} \\times \\pi \\times 25 \\times 10^{-20} \\times 1.38 \\times 10^5}$<br>Numerator: $433.32 \\times 10^{-23}$<br>Denominator: $1.414 \\times 3.14159 \\times 34.5 \\times 10^{-15} = 153.18 \\times 10^{-15}$<br>$\\lambda = \\frac{433.32 \\times 10^{-23}}{153.18 \\times 10^{-15}} = 2.83 \\times 10^{-8}$ m = $2\\sqrt{2} \\times 10^{-8}$ m","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41044,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/zJgyStmMoSAI9CnnmK3J33ymTJKLlL0zuxL845UjT3k.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/iMo2uRdEPCqD_4WNDDd6dfPA_6FggP6Pwg0z9FliiGU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Z4vg1vz0FGfwtyXeYAYyZGj_8BdFwv24_IDsMLavVOc.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/WqyHpCTtGM_tRTUcmELIumLNcpQWRoND7dXhENd8plQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{ms}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{3 \\mathrm{RT}}{\\mathrm{M}}} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{~V}_{\\mathrm{rms}}^2=3 \\mathrm{RT} / \\mathrm{M}\n\\end{aligned}$\n\nHence we can conclude that $\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{rms}}^2$ is directly proportional to temperature\n$\\mathrm{y}=\\mathrm{mx}$\n$\\Rightarrow$ Graph will be straight line","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41073,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>11</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The internal energy of a gas is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>.</p><p>A diatomic gas has&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;translational and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;rotational degrees of freedom. A monoatomic gas has&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;translational degrees of freedom.</p><p>Hence, the internal energy of the mixture&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msub><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41064,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>For both the gases, it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>.</p><p>Thus, from equation (1), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>16</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41100,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Using first law of thermodynamics,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>W</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>U</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>Q</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, molar heat capacity,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41045,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$127^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$117^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$-39^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$-78^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}& \\mathrm{K} . \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{\\mathrm{nf}_1 \\mathrm{RT}}{2} \\\\& \\mathrm{~T}_{\\mathrm{i}}=-78^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C} \\rightarrow 273+\\left[-78^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\\right]=195 \\mathrm{~K}\n\\end{aligned}$\nK.E $\\alpha \\mathrm{T}$\nTo double the K.E energy temp also become double\n$\\begin{aligned}& \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{f}}=390 \\mathrm{~K} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{~T}_{\\mathrm{f}}=117^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41067,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the average kinetic energy per molecule of a gas at any temperature&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>&nbsp;is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>avg</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math></p><p>where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;is Boltzmann constant.</p><p>From above equation, it can be concluded that the average kinetic energy per molecule is independent of the molecular weight of the gas.</p><p>Hence, the required ratio is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (15 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41179,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{(\\gamma-1)}{2 \\gamma \\mathrm{R}} \\mathrm{Mv}^2 \\mathrm{~K}$","$\\frac{\\gamma M v^2}{2 \\mathrm{R}} \\mathrm{K}$","$\\frac{(\\gamma-1)}{2 \\mathrm{R}} \\mathrm{Mv}^2 \\mathrm{~K}$","$\\frac{(\\gamma-1)}{2(\\gamma+1) R} \\mathrm{Mv}^2 \\mathrm{~K}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\mathrm{W}=\\Delta \\mathrm{U}$\n$\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{mv}^2=\\mathrm{nC}_{\\mathrm{v}} \\mathrm{dT}$\n$=\\frac{\\mathrm{m}}{\\mathrm{M}} \\frac{\\mathrm{R}}{\\gamma-1} \\mathrm{dT}$\n$\\mathrm{dT}=\\frac{\\mathrm{M}(\\gamma-1) \\mathrm{v}^2}{2 \\mathrm{R}} \\mathrm{K}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2011","image":null},{"id":41096,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p><p>As argon is monoatomic gas, so it has three degree of freedom <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>f</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and oxygen is a diatomic gas, so its degree of freedom is five.</p><p>We know that average kinetic energy per molecule is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></math>, where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is Boltzmann&#39;s constant and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>&nbsp;is temperature.</p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp;is fixed for both gas.</p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>Ar</mi></msub><msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41191,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["80 K","73 K","3 K","20 K"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{ms}} \\alpha \\sqrt{\\mathrm{T} / \\mathrm{m}} ; \\quad \\sqrt{\\frac{273+47}{32}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{T}{2}}$ or $\\mathrm{T}=20 \\mathrm{~K}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41126,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["continuously stick to the walls of container.","suffer change in momentum when impinge on the walls of container.","continuously lose their energy till it reaches wall.","are attracted by the walls of container."],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>From the assumption of KTG, the molecules of gas collide with the walls and suffers momentum change which results in force on the wall and hence pressure.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41093,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["The velocity of atomic oxygen remains same","The velocity of atomic oxygen doubles","The velocity of atomic oxygen becomes half","The velocity of atomic oxygen becomes four times"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The RMS velocity of a gas is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;dissociates into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>&nbsp;its&nbsp;molecular mass becomes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>. Therefore,</p><p>Ratio of RMS&nbsp;speed,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41082,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["Proportional to square of temperature (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>).","Inversely proportional to square root of&nbsp;temperature (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>).","Proportional to square root of temperature&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>T</mi></msqrt></math>.","Proportional to temperature&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>)</mo></math>."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Root mean&nbsp;speed of a gas molecule is stated as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>, where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is the universal gas constant, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> is&nbsp;temperature, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> is the molar&nbsp;mass of the gas.</p><p>Thus,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><msqrt><mi>T</mi></msqrt></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41110,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8073b2b5-f1b9-4bbb-a7b5-8e5d395d72ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 405px; height: 159px;\" /></p><p>Number&nbsp;of moles is conserved.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></msubsup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msubsup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn><mn>3</mn></msubsup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41170,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></math> <br/><br/> <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> ;  <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> ;  <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>  ;  <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> ;  <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41042,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["4205.5 J","4102.8 J","3582.7 J","3986.3 J"],"answer":1,"solution":"Kinetic energy of translation $=\\frac{3}{2} n R T$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& n=\\frac{50 \\mathrm{~g}}{44 \\mathrm{~g}}=\\frac{25}{22} \\mathrm{~mol} \\\\\n& T=17^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}=290 \\mathrm{~K}\n\\end{aligned}$\n$\\Rightarrow$ Kinetic energy of translation\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\frac{3}{2}\\left(\\frac{25}{22}\\right)(8.3)(290) \\mathrm{J} \\\\\n& =4102.8 \\mathrm{~J}\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41092,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>72</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Number of moles of Hydrogen <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p>Number of moles of oxygen&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>128</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>Using ideal gas equation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>,</p><p>Where pressure&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi>STP</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Putting the values,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>273</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>273</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41166,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math><math><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (08 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41186,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$3 / 2$","$23 / 15$","$35 / 23$","$4 / 3$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{Q}=\\mathrm{Q}_1+\\mathrm{Q}_2$\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_1+\\mathrm{n}_2}{\\gamma_{\\mathrm{m}}-1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_1}{\\gamma_1-1}+\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_2}{\\gamma_2-1}$\n$\\gamma_{\\mathrm{m}}=\\frac{3}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41076,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>, the rms speed is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>800</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>, the rms speed is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>800</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (2) by equation (1) and solve to calculate the required speed.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>800</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msqrt><mfrac><mn>800</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41164,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$1.3 \\times 10^4$","$1.3 \\times 10^5$","$1.3 \\times 10^2$","$1.3 \\times 10^3$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nv &=\\sqrt{3 k_{\\mathrm{B}} T / m_{\\mathrm{He}}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{3 \\times 1.4 \\times 10^{-23} \\times 300}{7 \\times 10^{-27}}} \\\\\n&=1.34 \\times 10^3 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":41039,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A-III, B-IV, C-I, D-II","A-III, B-II, C-IV, D-I","A-II, B-IV, C-I, D-III","A-IV, B-II, C-III, D-I"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\gamma=1+\\frac{2}{\\mathrm{f}}$<br/>$f=6$, Triatomic rigid gas<br/>$\\mathrm{f}=7$, Diatomic non-rigid gas<br/>$f=5$, Diatomic rigid gas<br/>$\\mathrm{f}=3$, monoatomic rigid gas<br/>$\\gamma=1+\\frac{2}{6}=\\frac{4}{3}$ (Triatomic)<br/>$\\gamma=1+\\frac{2}{7}=\\frac{9}{7}($ Diatomic, non-rigid $)$<br/>$\\gamma=1+\\frac{2}{5}=\\frac{7}{5}($ Diatomic, rigid $)$<br/>$\\gamma=1+\\frac{2}{3}=\\frac{5}{3}($ Monoatomic, rigid $)$<br/>A-III, B-IV, C-I, D-II","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41188,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{4}{3}$","2","$\\frac{5}{3}$","$\\frac{3}{2}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{P} \\propto \\mathrm{T}^3 \\quad\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1}{\\mathrm{P}_2}\\right)=\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{T}_1}{\\mathrm{~T}_2}\\right)^3$\nComparing it with standard eq. $\\frac{\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{p}}}{\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{v}}}=\\gamma=\\frac{3}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":41187,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{T}_1+\\mathrm{T}_2$","$\\left(\\mathrm{T}_1+\\mathrm{T}_2\\right) / 2$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{T}_1 \\mathrm{~T}_2\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1 \\mathrm{~V}_1+\\mathrm{P}_2 \\mathrm{~V}_2\\right)}{\\mathrm{P}_1 \\mathrm{~V}_1 \\mathrm{~T}_2+\\mathrm{P}_2 \\mathrm{~V}_2 \\mathrm{~T}_1}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{T}_1 \\mathrm{~T}_2\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1 \\mathrm{~V}_1+\\mathrm{P}_2 \\mathrm{~V}_2\\right)}{\\mathrm{P}_1 \\mathrm{~V}_1 \\mathrm{~T}_1+\\mathrm{P}_2 \\mathrm{~T}_2 \\mathrm{~T}_2}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41069,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>27</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The RMS speed is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>The average speed is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>avg</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>The ratio is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>22</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>33</mn><mn>28</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Comparing it with the given value&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>28</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</